    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>President Retiring From a BBDO Unit</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas H Carey, president of BBDO North America, part of BBDO Worldwide, is retiring, effective on July 1 (Advertising column) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Thomas H. Carey, president of BBDO North America, part of the BBDO Worldwide unit of the Omnicom Group, is retiring, effective on July 1, the agency said in a memo to employees.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Thomas H. Carey, president of BBDO North America, part of the BBDO Worldwide unit of the Omnicom Group, is retiring, effective on July 1, the agency said in a memo to employees.</p>
        <p>Mr. Carey, 55, joined the agency in 1990 as president and chief operating officer at the New York office. He rose to co-chief executive of the office in 1994 and became president at BBDO North America in 1996. Earlier this year, Mr. Carey took on new duties at BBDO Worldwide, while relinquishing his co-chief executive duties, as well as supervision of, BBDO New York.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
